# image 1
Style: Chinese Ink Wash (Sumi-e)
Aspect Ratio: 16:9
An artistic illustration of tea eggs (茶叶蛋) in a traditional street vendor setting: a large dark pot with steam rising, cracked eggshells showing marbled patterns, eggs bobbing in dark tea broth, warm morning light filtering through, subtle silhouettes of people in the background suggesting a bustling street scene, earthy browns and warm amber tones, wet-on-wet technique creating soft textures, peaceful yet lively atmosphere capturing everyday Chinese street food culture, high quality digital art, museum-poster feel.

# image 2
Style: Digital Illustration
Style: Chinese Ink Wash (Sumi-e)
Aspect Ratio: 16:9
A clean, educational illustration showing the contrast between gongfu cha tea ceremony and tea eggs: left side shows elegant gaiwan with delicate tea leaves and small cups in a meditative setting, right side shows casual tea eggs in a simple pot with cracked shells, both connected by tea leaves flowing between them, soft pastel colors with warm earth tones, minimalist composition emphasizing the bridge between refined tea culture and practical daily life, high quality digital art.
